  <other_name type="common_name">Cedar Breaks wild buckwheat</other_name>
  <discussion>Variety alpestre is the high-elevation expression of the species and is only marginally distinct. It is restricted essentially to the Cedar Breaks National Monument area of Iron County, where it is scattered but fairly common along the rim of the breaks. It is this component of the species that is now in cultivation.</discussion>
